## Feed tab — events + community posts

### How the feature works

- **Events** load from Firestore `events` (same schema as the digital curriculum admin events): `title`, `date`, `time`, `location`, `details`, `event_type`, `image_url`, `registered_users` (array of UIDs), optional `total_spots` / `available_spots`, `created_at`, `updated_at`. The list shows upcoming events (`date` on or after today). Tapping an event opens `/events/:eventId` (detail, register/unregister via `arrayUnion` / `arrayRemove` on `registered_users`).
- **Posts** use collection `feed_posts` with `post_category`, `post_title`, `post_details`, `author_id`, `author_name`, `created_at`, `updated_at`. Categories match the digital curriculum discussion list (`lib/data/feed_post_categories.dart`). **Likes** are stored under `feed_posts/{id}/likes/{userId}`; **replies** under `feed_posts/{id}/replies/{replyId}` with `body`, `author_id`, `author_name`, `created_at`. Reply likes use `replies/.../likes/{userId}`.
- **Routes:** `/feed/post/create` (new post), `/feed/post/:postId` (thread: full post, like, reply, like replies). FAB: **Posts** tab → new post; **Events** tab → `/events/create`; **All** tab → bottom sheet (new post or new event). **Opening the same post again** uses a unique query on the URL (`?_=<timestamp>`) and a `MaterialPage` keyed by the full URI so GoRouter does not reuse the same page key for identical paths (avoids the same post failing to open until much later).
- **Profile modal:** Tap a post author (avatar/name) on the feed or post detail to open a read-only profile sheet (same seven onboarding sections + achievements + certificates, no edit). **Message** is a full-width row under the title (not squeezed into the top bar) and opens `/messages/direct/{userId}` when signed in and the profile is not yours; auth is driven by `authStateChanges()` so the button appears once Firebase Auth has the user. Email is omitted when viewing someone else’s profile.
- **Events list:** Loads **every** document in `events` (no `orderBy` filter that drops docs missing `date`); sorted in the client by `date` when present.
- **Replies:** `author_name` is resolved from `users/{uid}` via `UserProfileRepository.getDisplayNameForUser`. Nested replies store optional `parent_reply_id` on the reply doc; UI shows threads with indent and **Reply** on each comment.

## Security rules note

See repo root `firestore.rules` — currently **development-wide** open rules on a date predicate for the shared project. **`eligibleUsers` and `inviteCodes` must not be writable from the client** in production; use Admin SDK in Cloud Functions only. Merging production rules must account for the digital curriculum web app in the same database. Details: `EXPANSION_INVITE_AUTH.md`.

Intended direction: `users/{userId}` **read** for any **authenticated** user (profile modal); owner write; feed/events rules as before.

## Development: Hot Restart vs Firebase (Android)

If you see:

`PlatformException(channel-error, Unable to establish connection on channel: ... FirebaseCoreHostApi.initializeCore ...)`

that usually happens after **Hot Restart**. Stop the app completely, then **Run** again (cold start). Prefer **Hot Reload** for UI work.

`lib/main.dart` skips `Firebase.initializeApp` when `Firebase.apps` is already populated, and logs a hint if init fails.
